.box
  .title.is-3.mb-2 DjMngr &middot; Doujinshi manager
  
  .block
    This application is made for doujin/manga/comics/novel readers and photographers to
    %strong manage a collection of zipped image sets
    , easying their work with sorting files, assigning metedata, searching, and
    reading online from any device.
  
  %hr
  
  .block
    As time passes by we accumulate more and more images,
    %em saving them individually
    on disk takes a lot of space, instead
    %em zipping each set/folder
    helps freeing a big chunk of disk space.
    %br
    Technically speaking we do not save much space by compressing images but instead
    by reducing unused space in disk blocks: each file does waste some space, so
    instead of
    %em a big number
    of files wasting precious KiB we only have a
    %em single one.
    This leads to a 10~20% of freed space,
    %a(href="https://dictionary.cambridge.org/dictionary/english/ymmv" target="_blank") YMMV
    \.
  .block
    In doing so arises the need of an application to easily view these compressed
    sets of images, in addition to DjMngr there are a miriad of options out there:
    
    %a(href="https://sourceforge.net/p/mcomix/wiki/Home/" target="_blank") MComix
    ,
    %a(href="https://www.faststone.org" target="_blank") FastStone MaxView
    ,
    %a(href="https://www.acdsee.com/en/products/acdsee-free/" target="_blank") ACDsee
    ,
    and
    %a(href="https://duckduckgo.com/?q=zip+image+viewer" target="_blank") more
    \; but
    %strong DjMngr
    %em has more to offer than a simple viewer!

